<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Book Notes</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="icon_path" type="image/icon type">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/main.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="nav-bar">
        <h2>Book notes</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="/new">New note</a></li>
                <li><a href="/about"></a>About</a></li>
            </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="hero">
        <h1>Books Review</h1>
        <p>Books have a way of pulling you into different worlds. Some stay with you, some don’t. Here, I share my thoughts on different books—what stood out, what didn’t, and whether they’re worth your time.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <% posts.forEach((post)=> {%>
        <div class="card" id="<%= post.id%>">
            <img src="/images/cat.jpg" alt="cat image" height="100px" width="100px">
            <h3><%= post.title%></h3>
            <small><%= post.date%></small>
            <small>Rating: <%= post.rating%>/10</small>
            <hr/>
            <p><%= post.intro%></p>
            <p><a href="/notes/:<%=post.id %>">Read notes</a></p>
        </div>
        <%})%>
    </div>
</body>
</html>